01:12.905 --> 01:14.260
It's one of the few places that carries

01:14.285 --> 01:16.215
- this bakery's muffins.
- Okay.

01:16.440 --> 01:17.875
Uh, hey, I-I'll see you, Rick.

01:17.900 --> 01:21.425
Anyway, about this
party tomorrow night...

01:21.900 --> 01:23.997
Oh, so you don't dress up
like a movie star,

01:24.038 --> 01:26.508
you dress up like a
character from a movie.

01:26.827 --> 01:30.315
I know that.
I'm going as Julia Roberts.

01:30.914 --> 01:34.063
- That's not a character.
- Well, I want to go as her.

01:34.643 --> 01:36.855
Last week my husband
told me that I looked

01:36.880 --> 01:38.526
like Julia Roberts from Pretty Woman.

01:38.553 --> 01:40.265
So go as Vivian Ward from Pretty Woman.

01:40.290 --> 01:42.963
Wait, he said you
looked like Julia Roberts

01:43.002 --> 01:45.613
- specifically in Pretty Woman?
- Mm-hmm.

01:45.819 --> 01:47.646
I think he might've been
trying to tell you

01:47.671 --> 01:49.238
that you were dressed like a whore.

01:52.255 --> 01:53.309
That's not a bad thing.

01:53.334 --> 01:54.581
- Really?
- No, it's good.

01:54.606 --> 01:56.521
They like that kind of stuff.

02:00.942 --> 02:02.739
What, are you fucking serious?

02:03.710 --> 02:06.417
Oh, my God, I am so sorry. I...

02:06.604 --> 02:08.326
Sorry.

02:08.424 --> 02:10.121
I thought you were...

02:10.419 --> 02:13.089
The kid lives over on Maple.

02:16.079 --> 02:17.888
I'm sorry, I apologize.

02:28.496 --> 02:30.411
I can't believe he took it.

03:38.314 --> 03:40.989
I'm paying you to find out
who my husband is screwing,

03:41.014 --> 03:43.180
not who he's screwing over.

03:43.281 --> 03:45.141
I told you where he was last night.

03:45.236 --> 03:46.989
He was pitching condos to brokers,

03:47.014 --> 03:49.712
one after another,
at the Fairmont Hotel bar.

03:50.142 --> 03:52.168
I watched him and he didn't
leave with any of them.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.138
Then you keep looking.

03:54.325 --> 03:56.284
He's a million miles away these days.

03:56.993 --> 04:00.501
He went on a diet.

04:00.894 --> 04:03.473
A man with his appetites
does not go on a diet.

04:03.594 --> 04:05.768
People's metabolisms change.

04:05.873 --> 04:08.005
Could it be somebody in his yoga class?

04:08.249 --> 04:10.207
Nah, I don't know why he does yoga.

04:10.511 --> 04:13.296
Not for the asses in yoga pants.

04:13.340 --> 04:15.203
He does yoga and he runs an hour

04:15.228 --> 04:16.958
on the treadmill every day
so that he looks good.

04:16.983 --> 04:18.920
Why does he want to look good?

04:19.346 --> 04:20.524
To get laid.

04:22.399 --> 04:26.229
- If you say so.
- Stay with him.

04:26.527 --> 04:28.224
We got the Abatsy party tomorrow night.

04:28.268 --> 04:29.672
I'll have eyes out, obviously,

04:29.697 --> 04:31.505
but maybe you could be on the grounds.

04:31.665 --> 04:34.709
- See what you see.
- Yeah. Sure.

04:34.858 --> 04:37.557
And that is for next week.

04:46.336 --> 04:48.629
What the fuck?

04:49.096 --> 04:51.769
Let me guess, no note.

05:33.875 --> 05:35.050
Hey, Dannie.

05:36.806 --> 05:39.504
Glad I ran into you here.

05:40.584 --> 05:43.629
- Did you run into me?
- No, not really.

05:43.952 --> 05:46.183
How's your day been?
Still like your new job?

05:46.363 --> 05:49.806
Yeah, yeah, he's, uh... he's a handful.

05:51.223 --> 05:54.024
Listen, remember when you asked

05:54.054 --> 05:55.925
what was the top piece of advice

05:55.989 --> 05:57.599
I wished I'd had
before I started college?

05:57.695 --> 06:00.153
Thank God. I was afraid
I was gonna have to wing it.

06:00.226 --> 06:03.119
Well, see, I realized that...

06:03.450 --> 06:04.974
it's to be sure and make new friends

06:04.999 --> 06:06.348
the summer before you leave.

06:06.758 --> 06:09.379
Hmm. You're volunteering?

06:09.430 --> 06:11.578
I-I am. I'm brave like that.

06:13.884 --> 06:15.712
Do you want to hang out later?

06:15.856 --> 06:17.817
Like, tonight later?

06:17.967 --> 06:21.034
Why not? Unless you-you have plans.

06:21.180 --> 06:23.031
No.

06:23.774 --> 06:26.163
Well, now you do.

07:12.519 --> 07:14.085
Another day, right, Dante?

07:14.129 --> 07:15.304
Sure enough.

07:15.484 --> 07:19.484
Garrett Drimmer, hold up a minute.

07:19.613 --> 07:20.788
Fuckin' Walsh.

07:20.813 --> 07:21.964
See how he did that?

07:21.989 --> 07:25.123
Now you got to talk to him
on your own time.

07:28.158 --> 07:30.378
Hours have to be cut.

07:30.481 --> 07:32.806
And fingers are pointing
at the material handlers.

07:32.930 --> 07:36.767
I only got 50, 55 total
for you and Dante.

07:36.934 --> 07:38.762
You've been here longer.

07:39.405 --> 07:41.534
I know yinz two is friends.

07:41.656 --> 07:45.094
And don't worry, there is one option.

07:45.465 --> 07:47.327
You both cut eight to ten a week.

07:47.352 --> 07:49.400
I could make a case
to keep yous both on.

07:49.443 --> 07:50.980
Hours are money.

07:51.046 --> 07:55.572
All right, but I-it's your call.
I'm gonna have to cut him loose.

07:55.636 --> 07:57.320
Wait, wait, what'd you say, uh, 55?

07:57.377 --> 07:58.675
Yeah.

07:59.506 --> 08:01.713
Well, that-that means
with, uh, with him gone,

08:01.738 --> 08:03.479
I'm ripe for some OT?

08:05.713 --> 08:07.402
Yeah, I expect so.

08:07.462 --> 08:10.910
That's good.
Yeah, count me in for that.

08:14.058 --> 08:17.235
Hey. I got the car today.
You want a lift?

08:17.293 --> 08:19.645
Uh, man, y-you go ahead.

08:20.207 --> 08:22.818
Yeah, uh, walking keeps me motivated.

08:23.034 --> 08:24.732
Okay.

08:47.135 --> 08:48.548
Hey. GARRETT: Hey.

08:48.609 --> 08:50.001
She had a good nap today.

08:50.032 --> 08:52.861
- Aw, that's good.
- Yeah. Uh...

08:53.325 --> 08:56.400
You know, my husband was
watching this special on rheas,

08:56.467 --> 08:58.527
or ray-as, some are like ostriches.

08:58.581 --> 09:01.242
- Uh-huh.
- And the father rhea,

09:01.267 --> 09:02.834
takes care of them little ones,

09:02.859 --> 09:04.513
like from eggs on.

09:05.540 --> 09:08.239
But people ain't supposed
to be like that.

09:09.265 --> 09:10.767
Uh, well...

09:10.811 --> 09:12.637
- Here I am.
- Yeah.

09:12.662 --> 09:15.694
Well, I'm just saying,
we feel really bad for you,

09:15.854 --> 09:18.589
and we love having
little Carrie here now,

09:18.639 --> 09:21.322
but if you don't get caught up...

09:21.355 --> 09:23.465
Yeah... For a minute there,

09:23.490 --> 09:25.340
I thought you were being nice.

09:25.462 --> 09:29.097
Oh... Here. Look.

09:29.477 --> 09:31.557
You know, you could...

09:31.670 --> 09:33.187
No, I......take it if you want.

09:33.255 --> 09:36.619
- Yeah, no, I want what you owe me.
- Payday is next week.

09:36.644 --> 09:37.902
- Garrett, I heard that before,
- I'll-I'll have it then.

09:37.926 --> 09:38.981
I heard it before.

09:39.006 --> 09:41.081
Next week, or don't
bring her by no more.

09:41.138 --> 09:42.614
If I can't leave her
with somebody, then I can't...

09:42.638 --> 09:44.839
Yeah. Well, sorry.

09:45.873 --> 09:47.712
All right, look, um...

09:48.291 --> 09:50.641
You know, I'm-I'm fixing up
my dirt bike.

09:51.112 --> 09:52.287
I'm gonna sell it.

09:52.863 --> 09:54.093
- Okay.
- Okay?

09:54.161 --> 09:55.916
Okay, all right...

09:58.135 --> 10:00.268
What do you think? Let's go for a walk.

10:05.008 --> 10:07.271
I think it's over there.

10:08.889 --> 10:10.672
Whoa!

11:36.298 --> 11:37.798
- Hey.
<i>- Garrett.</i>

11:37.855 --> 11:41.772
<i>I need you to-to come down
to the mill right away.</i>

11:42.123 --> 11:44.081
What?

11:44.492 --> 11:46.278
<i>I'm in trouble.</i>

11:46.342 --> 11:47.596
Yeah, wait, uh, y-yeah.

11:47.621 --> 11:49.647
What happened?

11:49.899 --> 11:52.033
<i>Can you just come down here?
You got to help me.</i>

11:52.117 --> 11:54.786
- Uh, right now?
<i>- Yes. Right now.</i>

11:54.849 --> 11:56.805
Wh... uh, what...?

11:57.059 --> 12:00.105
I can't come right now.
I got, I got Carrie.

12:00.334 --> 12:01.683
<i>Can you just...?</i>

12:06.530 --> 12:08.479
<i>Garrett, it's got to be you.</i>

12:08.598 --> 12:11.949
- Yeah, um...
- <i>I really need your help.</i>

12:14.095 --> 12:16.190
<i>Garrett, I need you.</i>

12:16.309 --> 12:18.213
Can you just, like, give me like 15...?

12:18.309 --> 12:20.099
<i>Yeah. Yeah, just...</i>

12:20.124 --> 12:21.583
<i>don't tell anybody where
you're going, all right?</i>

12:21.607 --> 12:24.697
Can you... yeah, just give me
like, give me like, uh,

12:24.754 --> 12:28.453
15 minutes, I'll...
and I'll be there, okay?

13:26.327 --> 13:28.048
Shh. Hey, hey.

13:28.116 --> 13:30.423
Quiet, quiet, quiet. Okay.

13:32.872 --> 13:34.749
So you've never snuck in here before?

13:34.774 --> 13:35.883
No.

13:35.908 --> 13:37.983
Cool, so I get points
for originality then.

13:38.078 --> 13:40.776
Unlike me, with the movie I chose.

13:41.121 --> 13:43.128
I hate how I always know
exactly what's about to happen

13:43.153 --> 13:45.155
but I still get scared.

13:47.122 --> 13:49.029
So you're going off to Michigan.

13:49.125 --> 13:50.910
- Right?
- Yeah.

13:51.134 --> 13:52.539
It's your last summer here.

13:52.605 --> 13:54.106
Mm.

13:55.746 --> 13:58.669
You know... the summer
before I started at Pitt,

13:58.694 --> 14:01.164
- my parents split up.
- Shit.

14:01.776 --> 14:04.365
Sorry, they couldn't
have waited three months?

14:04.408 --> 14:06.193
That's exactly what I said.

14:07.585 --> 14:08.935
You must've freaked out.

14:09.050 --> 14:10.937
- It's tough.
- Mm.

14:10.980 --> 14:12.735
Like, it-it totally sucks.

14:12.798 --> 14:15.148
I bet, but it must have made you

14:15.173 --> 14:17.175
even more excited to go to school.

14:17.378 --> 14:20.076
Yeah, that and a couple
of handles of vodka later,

14:20.391 --> 14:22.122
I was good to go.

14:22.165 --> 14:24.124
Did you do that whole frat thing
where you almost die

14:24.167 --> 14:25.858
from alcohol poisoning, too?

14:25.974 --> 14:27.976
Oh, God. Um...

14:29.781 --> 14:30.913
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

14:32.790 --> 14:34.438
See, this is, this is why I'm into you:

14:34.722 --> 14:36.397
I like the way you look at things.

14:36.544 --> 14:38.503
You're so upbeat.

14:39.813 --> 14:41.815
- I think we should go swimming.
- What?

14:41.840 --> 14:44.779
- I-I don't have my suit...
- Uh, you know what? Neither do I,

14:44.840 --> 14:46.936
but that's what underwear's for.

14:54.420 --> 14:57.040
So, you said you were into me.

14:57.298 --> 14:58.865
It was just the vodka talking.

14:58.890 --> 15:00.544
You didn't have any vodka.

15:00.653 --> 15:02.089
Oh, shit.

15:02.245 --> 15:03.812
Hey.

15:03.930 --> 15:05.067
What was that for?

15:05.092 --> 15:07.269
Not just saying,
"Yeah, Dannie, I'm into you."

15:07.351 --> 15:10.317
Yes, Dannie. I'm into you.

15:47.698 --> 15:49.731
Fuck.

16:23.091 --> 16:25.877
What?

16:26.028 --> 16:28.248
- Are you... Are you ticklish?
- N-No.

16:28.291 --> 16:29.778
Is that, is that what's happening?

16:29.803 --> 16:31.085
- No, no, it's...
- No, no, no? Really?

16:31.109 --> 16:32.126
- You sure about that?
- No, stop.

16:32.151 --> 16:34.950
Stop, no! Stop. No, don't.

16:34.994 --> 16:37.039
Don't, don't, don't! Oh, oh!

16:37.249 --> 16:40.426
Stop! Stop, stop! No!

16:45.339 --> 16:48.037
Hey! Boy!

17:01.107 --> 17:03.413
Oh, fuck...

17:03.983 --> 17:06.898
Stop! Stop!

17:18.950 --> 17:21.387
Shit. I'm sorry.

18:36.643 --> 18:38.484
Man, I was hearing all last week

18:38.509 --> 18:40.030
that there might be layoffs.

18:40.080 --> 18:41.296
Yeah, me, too.

18:41.321 --> 18:43.149
Although, poker last night,

18:43.861 --> 18:45.540
Walsh says, "Looks like
we might be getting"

18:45.565 --> 18:47.200
a new order in from Vancouver."

18:47.256 --> 18:48.366
What?

18:48.398 --> 18:51.184
Bill told me.
He says to Walsh, "Hey, Walsh."

18:51.242 --> 18:53.916
"Last Wednesday, you were
having sex with your wife,

18:53.979 --> 18:55.460
"you left the curtains open.

18:55.527 --> 18:57.546
Whole neighborhood could
see you having sex."

18:57.654 --> 18:59.473
They're all laughing about it.

18:59.863 --> 19:02.014
Walsh is like, "Wait, what day?"

19:02.085 --> 19:03.695
He says, "Wednesday."

19:03.911 --> 19:05.872
Walsh says, "Oh, joke's on them."

19:05.952 --> 19:07.252
I wasn't home on Wednesday."

19:11.100 --> 19:13.494
What the fuck?

19:15.719 --> 19:17.721
Jesus.

19:34.651 --> 19:37.001
No guns. No casings.

19:37.877 --> 19:39.961
No body.

19:40.464 --> 19:43.007
Looks like whoever
was bleeding was dragged,

19:43.603 --> 19:44.998
loaded into the vehicle,

19:45.023 --> 19:47.004
which was then driven out that gate.

19:47.584 --> 19:48.946
Get a mold of the tracks.

19:48.977 --> 19:50.359
Measure the axle width.

19:50.388 --> 19:52.260
Looks like a cube truck, Chief.

19:52.376 --> 19:54.042
Make sure. Up there it looks like

19:54.067 --> 19:55.460
someone tried to wipe up the prints.

19:55.485 --> 19:57.299
Probably ran out
of nighttime, had to bail.

19:57.464 --> 19:59.045
Well, we got those
footprints over there.

19:59.110 --> 20:00.288
Those are from the two mill workers

20:00.313 --> 20:02.375
who found the scene this morning.

20:02.808 --> 20:04.090
It's human.

20:04.170 --> 20:05.506
Fuck.

20:05.583 --> 20:07.846
This much blood,
it's got to be a murder.

20:08.163 --> 20:10.268
Can tell you more in... four hours.

20:10.301 --> 20:11.868
- All right.
- Everything by overnight.

20:11.951 --> 20:13.604
Thanks for helping out.

20:13.895 --> 20:16.202
You want dogs to search for a body?

20:16.877 --> 20:18.979
Or bodies... this is a lot of blood.

20:19.127 --> 20:20.888
They probably can't get
to it till tomorrow,

20:20.913 --> 20:23.437
but ask those boys to
drag the river, huh?

20:23.494 --> 20:24.757
All right, Rook, you're with me.

20:24.782 --> 20:26.355
We're gonna talk to Bud Carl.

20:26.562 --> 20:29.043
- You ever met him?
- Me? Different planets.

20:29.107 --> 20:30.586
Know the family name, of course.

20:30.611 --> 20:31.891
Father opened the mill, right?

20:31.951 --> 20:35.041
Grandfather. He's number three.

20:37.105 --> 20:39.281
<i>What, on the mill grounds?</i>

20:39.553 --> 20:41.780
<i>I'll bet Bud isn't happy about that.</i>

20:41.990 --> 20:44.373
<i>Uh, they say
that they'll know more soon.</i>

20:44.417 --> 20:45.896
<i>I'll keep you updated.</i>

20:45.940 --> 20:48.824
<i>Ah, thanks for the heads-up.</i>

20:48.898 --> 20:50.454
<i>Well, right, yeah,
if the mill goes away,</i>

20:50.479 --> 20:52.268
<i>that would be great for us,</i>

20:52.293 --> 20:54.795
but crime is never good
for real estate.

20:55.191 --> 20:56.671
<i>We'll talk at the office.</i>

20:56.696 --> 20:58.538
<i>Uh, I can't come in to work today.</i>

20:58.586 --> 21:00.283
<i>What? Why not?</i>

21:01.565 --> 21:03.853
I have food poisoning or something.

21:03.928 --> 21:06.409
I-I can't leave the house.

21:28.522 --> 21:30.959
We had a shipment
go out, then shut down.

21:31.202 --> 21:32.828
Nobody was here after that.

21:32.888 --> 21:34.502
No security?

21:34.539 --> 21:36.559
Oh, geez. We haven't bothered

21:36.584 --> 21:37.896
to have a night guy for years.

21:37.921 --> 21:39.823
What are they gonna steal, the furnace?

21:39.848 --> 21:41.388
What time did the shipment go out, sir?

21:41.413 --> 21:43.328
About 10:15. Then I went home.

21:43.570 --> 21:45.525
I thought I was the last to go.

21:45.674 --> 21:48.590
Um, is that the usual time?

21:49.545 --> 21:51.144
It was a little late.

21:52.091 --> 21:55.150
There was a cancellation, last minute.

21:55.385 --> 21:57.159
The specs on one of the crates was off.

21:57.252 --> 21:59.033
You got any suspicion at all

21:59.058 --> 22:01.433
that maybe one of your workers
decided to take advantage

22:01.458 --> 22:04.331
of the mill being
so deserted down that end?

22:04.373 --> 22:06.287
- Like drugs and that?
- Yeah.

22:06.412 --> 22:08.256
I hear anything about that...

22:08.449 --> 22:11.119
- I... I call you.
- Right.

22:11.265 --> 22:13.078
Look, I'll help however I can.

22:13.157 --> 22:14.884
You want me to shut down the mill,

22:14.945 --> 22:16.462
the guys are gonna lose
a bunch of hours,

22:16.487 --> 22:19.115
- but I'll bank that furnace.
- Ah, thanks, Pop, but...

22:19.182 --> 22:20.822
shut you down for two days?

22:20.847 --> 22:22.815
Uh, cops are unpopular enough

22:22.840 --> 22:24.447
without taking bread
out of people's mouths.

22:24.500 --> 22:26.997
I don't know, I'll keep
my eyes and ears open.

22:27.934 --> 22:29.837
Somebody killed here.

22:33.568 --> 22:35.619
Figure out what happened, Chief.

22:36.237 --> 22:37.885
I intend to.

22:39.964 --> 22:41.272
Thank you for your time.

22:41.575 --> 22:43.446
Thank you, sir.

22:44.216 --> 22:45.956
Thank you, sir.

22:59.727 --> 23:01.287
Not surprised he got emotional.

23:01.340 --> 23:02.469
That's Bud, all right.

23:02.512 --> 23:04.079
You called him Pop.

23:04.163 --> 23:05.510
Just slipped out.

23:05.601 --> 23:07.254
All his workers call him Pop.

23:07.352 --> 23:09.223
Bud really cares about his people.

23:09.388 --> 23:11.999
Dogs are here, and the tire
tracks are from a cube truck.

23:12.188 --> 23:13.899
Put that out to our guys in the county.

23:13.924 --> 23:15.922
We are looking for a cube truck.

24:01.890 --> 24:03.224
That's Pop.

24:03.267 --> 24:04.783
Oh, here comes Pop.

24:06.744 --> 24:08.447
Hey, sorry, Pop, if we...

24:08.490 --> 24:10.536
Man, we didn't know what to do.

24:10.636 --> 24:12.462
We seen all that blood, we panicked.

24:12.487 --> 24:14.184
Hey. Yinz did the right thing.

24:14.314 --> 24:17.099
I don't give a fuck
how much trouble this causes.

24:17.456 --> 24:19.109
Listen up.

24:19.769 --> 24:21.407
This thing...

24:21.634 --> 24:23.457
it won't cost none of yinz a penny.

24:23.626 --> 24:25.237
All your jobs are safe.

24:25.507 --> 24:27.027
Promise you that.

24:28.731 --> 24:29.970
Thanks, Pop.

24:30.035 --> 24:32.170
Yeah. Sorry anyway, though.

24:32.206 --> 24:33.990
What'd the chief say, Pop?

